    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm experimenting with the newly added virtual lines diagnostic renderer and here's the config that I'm using:\n```lua\n  virtual_lines = {\n    current_line = true,\n    format = function(diagnostic)\n      local icon = severity_info[diagnostic.severity].icon\n      return ('%s %s: %s [%s]'):format(icon, diagnostic.source, diagnostic.message, diagnostic.code)\n    end,\n  }\n```\n\nNotice that I'm providing a custom `format` function that renders the diagnostic message as `<icon> <source>: <message> [<code>]` but it seems that the diagnostic code is being special cased when rendering which I'm not sure why:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a49f95d887a2425f11cb4a9b38f7b0039e4d837f/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua#L1855-L1859\n\nSo, we then see the following where the message has been prefixed with the diagnostic code:\n\n<img width=\"1080\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1af4dc67-9d42-4221-9998-bd3bb3eae9a1\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUsing the below diagnostic config which is the simplified version of the above config:\n\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config {\n  virtual_lines = {\n    current_line = true,\n    format = function(diagnostic)\n      return ('%s: %s [%s]'):format(diagnostic.source, diagnostic.message, diagnostic.code)\n    end,\n  },\n}\n```\n\nOpen a buffer with multiple diagnostics on the same line.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expected the rendered message to be exactly same as what I've configured to be using the custom format function.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1756+gc091bc3b9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot relevant here\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.39.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source",
